p:
I am pleased that the National Pork Board has read the Mini-Monograph on Environmental Health Impacts of Concentrated Animal Feeding Operations (CAFOs) (
 Bunton et al. 2007; 
 Burkholder et al. 2007; 
 Donham et al. 2007; 
 Gilchrist et al. 2007; 
 Heederik et al. 2007; 
 Thorne et al. 2007); I hope the board has given consideration to the 26 recommended priority research needs and 16 recommendations for translating science to policy. These were carefully developed by the 31 authors in the five workgroups on Airborne Exposures, Monitoring and Modeling, Water Quality, Infectious Disease Epidemics and Antibiotic Resistance, and Community Health.
